main event: Dr. Gordon V. Mohr and his wife observed a cigar-shaped object with pulsating lights and a trailing orange flame in Wisconsin on September 22, 1957.
interesting points: The cigar-shaped object was seen for a duration of 20 minutes., The object had pulsating lights similar to a jet., The sighting location was near West Bend Road, Wisconsin., Insufficient data was available for evaluation according to the report., They did not have any photographs to document the sighting.
sighted object: cigar-shaped object with pulsating lights and trailing orange flame
witness description: Dr. Gordon V. Mohr and his wife
